<subSubSection id="FBFF0F9051A057E2AE82774A42814F5F" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnostic description">
<paragraph id="6DC74BD7B184A02B99B3A8CA5BF7829F" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8ACE741991D0FB6633E838F776E542AC" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="65E3B9A629409C238160D3BE872CBFB6" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mandible lacinia mobilis a long, slender robust seta</emphasis>
. Maxilla 1 inner plate with pappose setae lining inner margin; palp 2-articulate. Maxilla 2 inner plate broader than outer plate; inner plate slightly shorter than outer plate. Maxilliped palp article 4 well developed. Gnathopod 1 coxa large, margins strongly diverging distally proximally slender, strongly broadened distally; dactylus small, simple, highly modified with blunt apical tip. Pereopod 3 carpus short to compressed, about as long as wide. 
<emphasis id="A50911745C90E8B6A9D09B2DF5D4A9D4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Pereopod 4 coxa with weakly-developed, subacutely produced posteroventral lobe</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDA29666ED0F98D2A88CF4E616EBF2EB" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="44B6587BBDBC437F36DBBFB97CEC6EE3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F94E61D9388F4C13DDD89371461C540" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
This monotypic taxon is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="5D17109D1761999B364ECEAA4C9272F0" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75347C32036A3380B57CAE7FE499CC3B" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Scopelocheiropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schellenberg, 1926. The main diagnostic character is the form of the lacinia mobilis, which is a long, narrow robust seta in 
<taxonomicName id="CEB5DF94191077668D701D9677E3BD22" authorityName="Dahl" authorityYear="1959" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0F8A91459AC7D3A189A6C81ABE9BF189" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bathycallisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, compared with a stemmed and distally expanded 
<normalizedToken id="84658B87C75EA949ED77693E4CF2A210" originalValue="‘blade’">'blade'</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4E542B7CBFFDFE35DD42950D7E7B7FAB" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23FA3C8F640EA66253373AD89DBD8890" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Scopelocheiropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Aside from this, there is a large difference in body size of these animals, 
<taxonomicName id="F1696E6B8943B4D27BB995602E4BB54D" baseAuthorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" baseAuthorityYear="1958" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Bathycallisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bathycallisoma schellenbergi" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schellenbergi">
<emphasis id="912C3071492AD3F8A7F043B3ACD66DA1" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bathycallisoma schellenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being an order of magnitude larger than any 
<taxonomicName id="EB285BC9FD9810B274B9D83C3D17FFBE" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19BFB0FB931448F30DAB36383070CE0" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Scopelocheiropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
